<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-30T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-30T21:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9106: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-31T10:00:00+08:00">July 31, 1937—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 31—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7. City quiet today. Some firing during the night as Japanese cleared
                                out some remnants of <hi rend="italic">Paoantui</hi> or other
                                hostile Chinese from the Chinese city. Japanese yesterday afternoon
                                completed destruction of Nankai University by artillery fire, air
                                bombing and burning, and bombarded several buildings in the Chinese
                                City, particularly Nankai middle school and girls school.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>